<DocsLayout title="Quick Start">
  <h1>Quick Start</h1>

  <p class="lead text-xl text-neutral-600">
    Get Ender up and running in 5 minutes using Docker.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Docker and Docker Compose installed</li>
    <li>An Android phone with a SIM card (or USB modem)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Clone the repository</h2>

  <pre><code class="language-bash">git clone https://github.com/ender-sms/ender.git
cd ender</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Start the services</h2>

  <pre><code class="language-bash">docker compose up -d</code></pre>

  <p>This starts:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Ender API server on port <code>8000</code></li>
    <li>Web dashboard on port <code>5173</code></li>
    <li>PostgreSQL database</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Create your first user</h2>

  <pre><code class="language-bash">docker compose exec backend python -m app.cli create-user \
  --email admin@example.com \
  --password your-password \
  --superuser</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Connect a device</h2>

  <p>
    Install the Ender Android app on your phone:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>Download the APK from <a href="https://github.com/ender-sms/android/releases">GitHub Releases</a></li>
    <li>Open the app and enter your server URL</li>
    <li>Log in with your credentials</li>
    <li>Grant SMS permissions when prompted</li>
  </ol>

  <p>Your phone is now registered as a device and ready to send messages.</p>

  <h2>5. Send your first message</h2>

  <p>First, get an API key from the dashboard at <code>http://localhost:5173</code>.</p>

  <p>Then send a message:</p>

  <pre><code class="language-bash">curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/sms \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"{"}
    "to": "+1234567890",
    "message": "Hello from Ender!"
  {"}"}'</code></pre>

  <p>You'll get a response like:</p>

  <pre><code class="language-json">{"{"}
  "id": "msg_abc123",
  "status": "queued",
  "to": "+1234567890",
  "message": "Hello from Ender!",
  "device_id": "dev_xyz789",
  "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>6. Check message status</h2>

  <pre><code class="language-bash">curl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/sms/msg_abc123 \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY"</code></pre>

